summary: Physiotherapy staff at the Waikato District Health Board are set to strike - 18-Nov-2018
title: Physiotherapy staff at the Waikato District Health Board are set to strike - 18-Nov-2018
body:
Physiotherapy staff at the Waikato District Health Board are set to strike – 18-Nov-2018

[ad_1]

Workers are seeking higher pay to keep up with the rising cost of living.

APEX union advocate, Luke Coxon, says around 50 staff will walk off the job.

He says the DHB is refusing to bargain, and the workers have been left with no choice.

The strike starts at 7 tomorrow morning and runs for 24 hours.

[ad_2]

Source link

title: NFL Injury Report: Chris Godwin, Sammy Watkins, John Ross, Keke Coutee for Week 11 https://ift.tt/eA8V8J
description:
Leading up to Week 11, fantasy owners had some injury concerns, but many of these players were removed from the injury report. For example, Adam Thielen had limited practices, but is not on the final injury report. Joe Mixon was downgraded in Thursday’s practice, raising eyebrows, but he also was not on the final injury report.
